Researchers have found a link between paternal age and schizophrenia risk, with older fathers contributing to an increased likelihood of the disorder.
The cannabis consumed today is much stronger than in the past, leading to underestimated psychological harm and fatal accidents.
Concern over cannabis has prompted a government campaign in France to highlight its dangers.
Breakthrough research in Australia has connected thinning grey matter in the brain to impaired thought processes in schizophrenia.
Additionally, a genetic region promoting fertility and longevity has been discovered in Europeans.
The Blue Brain Project aims to create a detailed model of the neocortex to simulate brain processes at the molecular level.
